<br>
(Full blown Hate raid.  Magi P'tasa is a mini-boss mob in Hate, not to be underestimated, but stories I have read were successful for the most part.)<br>
<br>
~~~*~~~*~~~*~~~<br>
<br>
The Staff of Elemental Mastery: Water is dropped from Phinigel Autropos. The Phinigel Autropos is a very hard level 50 Wizard. He can be taken out by around 2-3 groups that work well together. He enjoys dispelling people (usually your enduring breath.) He is also very difficult to kill because he is guarded by 6 guardians which can be hard to kill as well.<br>
<br>
(Phinny, 2 group minimum, raid level task.  His guards must be single pulled beneath the ledge where we would pull Phinny to.  Hit him hard, hit him fast.  After we pulled all but his last guard, we actually went in and had one tank take the last guard while the other tank and I worked on phinny till we could all focus on phinny.  Once there were two melee on Phinny, I could begin to work my magic of debuffing and then nuking.  After dropping him twice now, the method I like the best is single pulling the guards, all if possible, leaving one is ok as you can have someone charm the last guard, a great way to pet mez should a repop occur.  Once Phinny only has at max 1 guard left, CHARGE!)<br>
~~~*~~~*~~~*~~~<br>
<br>
The Crown of Elemental Mastery is dropped from anything on the 7th Island in Plane of Air. Basically, clearing the island can result in anywhere from 0-3 crowns. The crowns are not no drop, so they can be bought, but for extremely high prices.  aka, 150k pp.<br>
<br>
(MUCHO differing information throughout the web regarding just exactly which island these drop on.  I am going to hunt down some epic magi and milk them for info.  I will be back to edit this piece with my findings.)<br>
<br>
<br>
