HOW...Raid, Need a chanter and shammy for sure and mages with fire pets, main tank over 55, and as many healers and melee that we can get. Some tactics I've read: Most people pull him to skyfire zone before fightin, and report that he follows pullers reliably without aggroing additional mobs.  His magic resistance is reportedly average to below average for his lvl, and he is not immune to fire based spells, but cold magic recommeded.  Mage fire pets will be immune to his AE fire proc.  He will attempt to run when low on health, and he apparently has a high regen rate which will take affect near the end of the fight if he is not finished quickly. Slows debuffs highly recommended, charmed wurms do good damage as well.  Also that all melee cept main tank should attack form behind to avoid being hit by riposte. <br>
<br>
WHERE...Chardok<br>
WHO...Overking Bathezed, lvl 63, melee dmg max 385, casts fiery death(ae approx 500hp dmg, cancels one buff), complete heal, gravity flux, and gate.<br>
WHEN  -<br>
